- Fcitx needs non-POSIX and non-C locales, please generate locales first.
- Add the following to your ~/.xinitrc:

	export XMODIFIERS=@im=fcitx
	export GTK_IM_MODULE=fcitx
	export QT_IM_MODULE=fcitx
	LANG=`your langauge` fcitx -d

- For diagnosing any problem, run `fcitx-diagnose` .
- Pinyin is natively built-in. For other language support, file an issue at #6c37 .
